# browser-use — Agent Browser Control via Chrome DevTools Protocol
# Every agent has eyes. You see what they see. All local, all free.

## Overview
Harbinger agents can control real Chrome browser instances via CDP.
No API keys. No rate limits. No black boxes. Just local Chrome.

Every agent gets its own browser — navigate, screenshot, click, type,
read console, inspect network traffic. True visual transparency.

## Architecture
```
AGENT (any)
  ↓ POST /api/browser/sessions
BROWSER MANAGER (Go backend)
  ↓ Chrome DevTools Protocol
CHROME INSTANCE (headless or visible)
  ↓ screenshots stream back
DASHBOARD (BrowserManager page — user sees everything)
```

## Browser Session Lifecycle

### 1. Create a browser session
```
POST {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions
{
  "name": "BREACH recon on target.com",
  "url": "https://target.com",
  "agentId": "{{AGENT_ID}}",
  "headless": false,
  "viewport": {"width": 1920, "height": 1080}
}
```
Returns: `{ "id": "browser-xxx", "status": "active", "cdpEndpoint": "ws://..." }`

### 2. Navigate to a page
```
POST {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions/{{SESSION_ID}}/navigate
{"url": "https://target.com/admin"}
```

### 3. Take a screenshot (visual proof)
```
POST {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions/{{SESSION_ID}}/screenshot
{"fullPage": true}
```
Returns: `{ "data": "base64-png-data...", "timestamp": "..." }`

### 4. Execute JavaScript in page context
```
POST {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions/{{SESSION_ID}}/execute
{"script": "document.querySelectorAll('input[type=password]').length"}
```
Returns: `{ "result": 2 }`

### 5. Click elements
```
POST {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions/{{SESSION_ID}}/click
{"selector": "#login-button"}
```

### 6. Type into inputs
```
POST {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions/{{SESSION_ID}}/type
{"selector": "#username", "text": "admin"}
```

### 7. Read console logs
```
GET {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions/{{SESSION_ID}}/console
```
Returns: `[{"level": "error", "message": "Uncaught TypeError...", "timestamp": 1708900000}]`

### 8. Inspect network traffic
```
GET {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions/{{SESSION_ID}}/network
```
Returns: `[{"method": "POST", "url": "/api/login", "status": 401, "size": 234, "time": 120}]`

### 9. Get page source
```
GET {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions/{{SESSION_ID}}/source
```
Returns: `{ "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>..." }`

### 10. Close session
```
DELETE {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browser/sessions/{{SESSION_ID}}
```

## Agent-Specific Browser Patterns

### PATHFINDER — Recon Browser
- Open target homepage, screenshot landing page
- Navigate to robots.txt, sitemap.xml
- Check response headers in network tab
- Enumerate visible links and forms
- Screenshot admin panels, login pages

### BREACH — Exploit Browser
- Navigate to endpoints with payloads in URL params
- Monitor console for XSS proof-of-concept execution
- Watch network for leaked tokens in responses
- Screenshot successful exploits for reports
- Type payloads into form inputs

### PHANTOM — Cloud Browser
- Navigate to cloud consoles (AWS, GCP, Azure)
- Screenshot exposed S3 buckets, open endpoints
- Check for misconfigured CORS via console errors
- Test presigned URL access

### SPECTER — OSINT Browser
- Navigate to social profiles, company pages
- Screenshot LinkedIn, GitHub, domain whois
- Collect metadata from loaded resources
- Archive pages via screenshot timeline

### CIPHER — Binary Browser
- Download and inspect web-served binaries
- Check content-type headers for served firmware
- Navigate to API docs for reverse engineering targets

### SCRIBE — Evidence Browser
- Screenshot all findings for final report
- Capture full-page screenshots of vulnerable pages
- Build visual timeline of exploitation chain
- Archive network requests as evidence

## Dashboard Integration
All browser sessions appear in the BrowserManager page:
- Live session list with agent indicators
- Visual viewport preview with screenshot feed
- Console log viewer with level filtering
- Network request inspector with method/status/size/time
- One-click screenshot capture

## Visual Workflows
Agents with browsers can chain visual actions:
```
1. PATHFINDER opens target.com → screenshots landing page
2. PATHFINDER finds /admin → broadcasts to BREACH
3. BREACH opens /admin → types SQLi in login form
4. BREACH screenshots error revealing db structure
5. All screenshots + console logs → SCRIBE report
```

## Stats Endpoint
```
GET {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browsers/stats
```
Returns: `{ "totalSessions": 4, "activeSessions": 3, "agentSessions": 3 }`

## Which Agents Have Browsers
```
GET {{HARBINGER_API}}/api/browsers/agents
```
Returns: `{ "agentBrowsers": { "pathfinder-id": [...], "breach-id": [...] } }`

## Key Principles
- No Brave API keys — use Chrome directly
- No OpenAI credits — local LLMs drive the agents
- No rate limits — it's your machine
- No black boxes — you see every screenshot, every request
- True transparency — console, network, DOM all visible

## Triggers
- channel: all
- events: browser.created, browser.screenshot, browser.navigate, browser.execute
- priority: high
